Data source and Data model 6

Now lets start building our dashboard:         

1. Get the excel file by clicking on the link here => Data Source , then download and save it on your computer .

 2.  Open power bi desktop and load the source file to power bi, that is  get data from website.

 3.  Start cleaning the table. Like removing blank rows and duplicates.






4. Create relationship between tables. Before that, lets create Calendar table and the calculation is attached below.

5. Click on the model section of the power BI and create a relationship between calendar table and the fact table (covid-19 in US). 


Calendar table creation:

Calendar = 
ADDCOLUMNS (
CALENDAR (Date(Year(Min('COVID-19 in US'[date])),Month(Min('COVID-19 in US'[date])),DAY(Min('COVID-19 in US'[date]))), Date(Year(Max('COVID-19 in US'[date])),Month(Max('COVID-19 in US'[date])),DAY(Max('COVID-19 in US'[date])))),
"Month number", FORMAT ( [Date], "MM" ),
"Month Year", FORMAT ( [Date], "MMMYYYY" ),
"Month", FORMAT ( [Date], "mmmm" ),
"Week Number", "Week-"&WEEKNUM( [Date] ),
"Week", WEEKNUM ( [Date]),
"Day Of Month", Month([DATE]) &"-"& FORMAT ( [Date], "dd" ),
"Year Quarter", FORMAT ( [Date], "YYYY" ) & "/Q" & FORMAT ( [Date], "Q" ),
"Year", FORMAT ( [Date], "YYYY" ))
